{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, the estimated parameters of vehicles, such as range, velocity, and angle, are beneficial to precise beam prediction.",
    "Wang et al. [140] proposed an ISACbased multi-target tracking scheme for vehicular networks, bypassing the frequent identity feedback and reducing the communication overheads.",
    "Smart manufacturingNowadays, in smart manufacturing, many tasks have been conducted by the intelligent robots to boost the production efficiency and reduce the cost.",
    "Nevertheless, intelligent robots should cooperate with each other to fulfill the complex tasks, which requires the high-resolution positioning and frequent information exchange [141,142].",
    "Fortunately, the ISAC not only can offer the high-quality and low-latency communication but also enable the high-resolution positioning and navigation, showcasing unique advantages [143]."
  ]
}